we ve already exceeded the earth s carrying capacity which has been estimated to be 3 billion people but carrying capacity is not absolute it can be extended
we now have 7 billion people soon to be 8
so we ve greatly exceeded the earth s default carrying capacity
that number 3 billion was based on the amount of nitrogen in earth s soil making it arable for growing food
naturally there s simply not enough nitrogen in the soil to feed the amount of people we have today
and through an energy intensive process called the haber basch process we ve synthesized nitrogen on an industrial scale
this is called nitrogen fixation and it requires fossil fuels the goal is to chemically separate nitrogen from oxygen so it can be used as fertilizer for plants

this all occurred around the beginning of the 20th century and in conjunction with leaps in modern medicine especially vaccination we ve been able to grow our population greatly higher than that original 3 billion limit
there are people who therefor wonder about the viability of an entire world of vegetarians because there s not enough land and the demand for fertilizer would be too great

peace disagreement arrupted between them after an incident involving andr√©s being evacuated from chiripo sparing the details it sounds like jorge s dad s siblings are petty and unloving anyway after swearing to cut off contact her son went and visited them which greatly upset her while the family drama played out back at la casa soto i did a bunch of pushups and arm exercises on the playground monkey bars eventually everyone collected themselves and we drove across the city and up into the hills outside san jos√© in an area between two large mound like volcanos we passed coffee fields and
